{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5d539c2a-9f9f-4313-88e2-fc8a58c5b56e","content":"In .NET 10 MAUI, the iOS-specific `ios:Page.UseSafeArea` was replaced with a **cross-platform** `SafeAreaRegions` property on `Page`.\n\n**Before (.NET 9):**\n```xml\n<ContentPage\n    xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n    ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"\n    ...>\n```\n\n**After (.NET 10):**\n```xml\n<ContentPage\n    SafeAreaRegions=\"All\"\n    ...>\n```\n\nYou can drop the `xmlns:ios` declaration entirely if it was only used for safe area.\n\n`SafeAreaRegions` is a flags enum — you can also be selective:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Only respect top and bottom safe areas -->\nSafeAreaRegions=\"Top,Bottom\"\n```\n\nAvailable values: `None`, `Left`, `Top`, `Right`, `Bottom`, `All`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f35adf9d-f501-41ff-a9e3-d29e39b0127b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET MAUI migration issue from .NET 9 to .NET 10 regarding safe area handling on iOS. This is a known change in .NET 10 MAUI.\n\nIn .NET 10, the `ios:Page.UseSafeArea` attached property was removed/deprecated. The replacement is to use the new `SafeAreaRegions` property on `Page` (or views), which is a cross-platform API.\n\nThe new API in .NET 10 MAUI uses `Page.SafeAreaRegions` which accepts values like `All`, `None`, `Left`, `Top`, `Right`, `Bottom`, etc.\n\n\nTo migrate, I need to replace the iOS-specific namespace and attached property with the cross-platform `SafeAreaRegions` property directly on the `ContentPage`, using the flags enum values like `All` to control which safe area regions to respect.","outputTokens":565,"requestId":"7FC9:3950:5F6FDB1:6863E61:69F159D5"},"id":"7d15d408-374b-43fd-aa87-c009a693678e","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:07:44.419Z","parentId":"1f65cf68-3717-48b1-9af2-46d58cff3644"}
